						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and not dated. It refers itself to the reign of the Noḻamba-Pallava king <hi rend="bold">Noḻambādhirāja</hi> and records the construction of a Vishṇu temple and a grant of land for the service of the god by <hi rend="bold">Kōṭayya,</hi> a <hi rend="italic">Daṇḍanāyaka</hi> of the <hi rend="bold">Ballaha</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.</hi> Rāshṭrakūṭa king), after obtaining it from the Noḻamba king. The <hi rend="italic">Mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Agaḻi</hi> are to protect the gift.</p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
